\b\fs48 \cf0 Toolbar 
\fs28 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri-720\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri-2174\partightenfactor0
\cf0 There are several components on the tool bar.  From left to right, the Date Box.  The Date Box is used for entering a date that will be displayed on the calendar.  The date should be entered in default computer date format and then press return.  You can also enter date offsets in the form of date plus number of days (d), weeks (w), months (m) or years (y).   For example, 2 weeks before Christmas would be entered, \'9312/25/2016, -2w\'94.  Or 33 days from now could be entered \'9333d\'94.   You can also use 5 or 6 business days, which will skip Saturdays and Sundays or just Sundays.  \'93+15b5\'94 will be 15 days from now skipping the weekends.  To find the day or week of the year, enter w33 or d150.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri-720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri-2159\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Next is a handy button that will go to the current date.  You can also press the dot on the calendar or the month label.\
\
These are followed by the current day of the year and the offset of the selected date in days.  \
\
And lastly is the settings button.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri-720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
