\b \cf0 \

\fs48 General
\fs28 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri-2159\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Automatically start VIstaClock at Login
\b0  \'96 Starts the program automatically when you log in to the computer.\
\

\b Automatically hide VistaClock
\b0  \'96 Automatically hides the panel when it loses focus.\
\

\b Keep on Top
\b0  \'96 Forces the panel to stay on top of all other windows.\
\

\b Use dark theme
\b0  \'96 Changes the panel to use a dark background.\
\

\b Use shadows 
\b0 \'96 Show panel fonts with a shadow.\
\

\b Use Large Fonts
\b0  \'96 Use large fonts on the panel.\
\
\

\b\fs48 Menu Bar
\fs28 \
\
Show Date Time
\b0  \'96 Show date and time on menu bar else, show just an icon.\
\

\b Use Black & White Icon
\b0  \'96 If showing just an icon instead of the date time, then show it as black and white.\
\

\b Show Week Number Icon
\b0  \'96 Show the current week number on the menu bar.\
\

\b Use Black & White Week Number Icon
\b0  \'96 If showing the week number icon, make it black and white.\
\

\b Display the time with seconds
\b0  \'96 Show seconds on the menu bar clock.\
\

\b Use a 24-hour clock
\b0  \'96 Use 24-hour clock on menu bar.\
\

\b Show AM/PM
\b0  \'96 Show AM/PM indicator on the menu bar.\
\

\b Show the day of the week
\b0  \'96 Show the day of week on the menu bar.\
\

\b Show date
\b0  \'96 Show the date on the menu bar.\
\

\b Show full month name
\b0  \'96 Use the full month name in the date on the menu bar.\
\

\b Show secondary clock
\b0  \'96 Show a small second clock on the menu bar.  This will show the short time zone name day of week and time.\
\

\b Zone
\b0  \'96 Select the time zone for the secondary clock.\
\
\

\b\fs48 Calendar
\fs28 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri-2159\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri-2159\partightenfactor0

\b \cf0 Show Calendar
\b0  \'96 Show a calendar on the panel.\
\

\b Show Week Number column
\b0  \'96 Show the week number column on the calendar.\
\

\b Show Event Indicators
\b0  \'96 Shows a blue dot next to the day if any of your calendars has an event on that day.\
\

\b Show Reminder Indicators
\b0  \'96 Shows a red dot next to the day if there are any reminders due on that day.\
\

\b Show Boxes
\b0  \'96 Show boxes around the days in the month.\
\

\b Use red highlights
\b0  \'96 Force the highlight colors to be red instead of the menu item color.\
\
\

\b Clock Faces \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri-2159\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf0 \
Use this selector to choose which clock face to use on the panel.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri-2159\partightenfactor0

\b \cf0 Use a 24-hour clock
\b0  \'96 Force the panel clocks to use 24-hour style text.\
\
\

\b\fs48 Clocks
\fs28 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri-2159\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf0 \
This is the list of clocks to be shown on the panel.  There are buttons for reordering the clocks and also a button to remove it from the list.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri-2159\partightenfactor0

\b \cf0 Label
\b0  \'96 You can label the clocks, as you like.  Pick a city or pick something meaning for you like a name.\
\

\b Zone
\b0  \'96 This is the time zone to use for the clock.\
\

\b Use second hand
\b0  \'96 Use this option to show a second hand on the clock.\
\
